{{wp|lang=ja|タチバナ}}
{{wp|Citrus tachibana}}
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|たちばな}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=たちはな|-}}.

Named after {{m|ja|田道間守|tr={{w|Tajimamori}}}}, a legendary figure mentioned in the ''{{w|Kojiki}}'' and the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}''; purportedly bringing back certain fruits, but not directly as ''tachibana'' by name.

Shortened to ''tachi'' for some compounds.

{{ja-noun|たちばな|タチバナ}}

# {{taxlink|Citrus tachibana|species|ver=190215}}, a [[species]] of [[wild]], [[green]], [[inedible]] [[citrus fruit]] [[native]] to [[Japan]]
#: {{synonyms|ja|大和橘|tr=Yamato tachibana}}
#: {{hypernyms|ja|蜜柑|tr=mikan}}
# {{synonym of|lang=ja|唐橘|tr=kara-tachibana}}: the {{vern|trifoliate orange}}, {{taxlink|Citrus trifoliata|species|ver=190215}}, ''syn.'' {{taxlink|Poncirus trifoliata|species}} 
# {{synonym of|lang=ja|花橘|tr=hanatachibana}}: ''tachibana'' [[flower]]s; {{taxlink|Ardesia crenata|species|ver=190215}}; {{taxlink|Ardesia japonica|species|ver=190215}}; a kind of {{m|ja|襲の色目|tr=kasane no irome||[[color]] [[combination]] by [[layer#Verb|layering]] of [[garment]]s}}
# {{lb|ja|sort=たちはな|archaic}} [[generic name]] for [[citrus fruit]]s that can be [[eat]]en [[raw]]
# a {{m|ja|家紋|tr=kamon||[[family]] [[crest]]}} with [[design]]s of ''tachibana'' [[flower]]s, [[fruit]]s, and [[leaf|leaves]]

